Finland's &lt;Kansallis-Osake-Pankki>said in a statement it is issuing 100 mln dlrs subordinatedbonds due 1994 with equity warrants in international marketswith maximum interest rate of 4-5/8 pct.    Pricing will probably be April 7, the statement said.    The new issue could raise the bank's share capital by 200mln Finnish marks from the present 2.26 billion, it said.    The statement said the issue followed up the 1986 tenderissuance involving the first non-restricted or free shares,which can be held by aliens.    The warrants entitle holders to subscribe for a maximum of10 mln free shares. Eight mln of the Bank's current 113 mlnshares are free shares, a spokeswoman said.    The float follows the signing by Finnish President MaunoKoivisto last Friday of legislation entitling aliens witheffect from next June 1 to own up to two fifths of the sharesin Finnish companies, with consent of the Council of State, asagainst one fifth although voting rights will be restricted. REUTER&#3;